<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-617-711  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 617 711.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  June 1989 v2 n6 p42(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Arriba provides simple information management. (personalinformation management software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shipley, Chris.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Good Software Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Arriba (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Personal Information Management SystemsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Arriba Provides Simple Information Management Managing personal informationis a hot topic, to be sure.andP;  And in this industry, where there's a hot topic,there's a throng of developers offering new products or repositioning oldones.andP;  Depending on whom you talk to, anywhere from four to more than 24personal information managers (PIMs) are available today.andM;The newest of these is Arriba, from the Good Software Corporation.andM;Compared with the top four PIMs (Agenda, Info-XL, GrandView, and IZE), Arribais clean and simple--and those are its strengths.andP;  It merges the best toolsof the old desktop organizers--phone lists, autodialers, to-do lists, andcalendars--with the contemporary PIMs' ability to organize information in avariety of ways, mix free-form and structured data, and do broad textsearches to find information.andM;Arriba organizes information by folders and notes.andP;  You can dumpinformation--including calendars and phone lists--into folders, add notes tofolders, and place folders within other folders.andP;  You find information byusing the free-form search function in the main menu.andM;Good Software could have gone a step further in the ease-of-use department byadding mouse support of the drop-down menus.andP;  But that's a minor gripe:Arriba's function-key-driven operation is straightforward, and the availablecommands always appear across the top of the screen.andM;Arriba doesn't offer the intelligence and data linking of the most popularPIMs, so it's probably not the best choice if you're tracking a lot ofinterwoven information bits.andP;  Yet it's simple to use and priced ($195) tomake the Big Four squirm, and therefore it's good choice for people who needto track both structured and free-form information but don't want to investthe time and expense that many PIMs require.andM;For more information contact the Good Software Corporation, in Dallas, at800-272-2773 or 214-239-6085.andO;</TEXT></DOC>